title: Grateful Dead Live at Tivoli Theater on 1972-04-14
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Me & My Uncle, Mr. Charlie, You Win Again, Black Throated Wind, Chinatown Shuffle, Loser, Me And Bobby McGee, Cumberland Blues, Playin' In The Band, Tennessee Jed, El Paso, Big Boss Man, Beat It On Down The Line, Casey Jones

Set 2

Truckin', It Hurts Me Too, Brown Eyed Women, Looks Like Rain, Dark Star-> Sugar Magnolia, Good Lovin'-> Caution (Do Not Stop on Tracks)-> Who Do You Love-> Caution (Do Not Stop on Tracks)-> Good Lovin', Ramble On Rose, Not Fade Away-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Not Fade Away, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Great show Really well done matrix. I actually prefer it over the official release. Thanks Dave usborne for your great work.

Jump on your pony and ride.. Pretty neat half the band mainly JERRY 
still in the Dark Star
as Sugar Magnolia got rolling. 
They don't have split transitions very often
but they are a trip when they happen.
Wow, PIG just rapping his butt off. 
There is so much music here. 
This 2nd set is even larger 
than the previous show in England.
"You are my sweet little mare
I ride you everywhere"
and the pc crowd didn't like Money ,Money?
Cherry Pie rap. Great separation so i can hear each musician interact with Pigpen/
Into Caution.
i wonder why they dropped Alligator?
surprised PIG never found his way back to it.
Phil just runs with that bass line.
Did you notice NFA is one  of the few tunes that PIG does backing vocals on for this tour.

So nice to have good sound for this Long ago, I had a soundboard of this show that was very high in pitch.  Like, a whole step, not a Half Step.  So nice to be able to stream that Dark Star and that Good Lovin' jam in good quality.  The Philo Stomp is not to be missed.  Pigpen's in his finest rappin' form on the Good Lovin' medley.  "Hop in the saddle and ride."
